ttention to manpower needs, and develops the concept of a health team that would include paramedical as well as professional personnel. He also proposes a plan for medical education that would be devoted to meeting a particular country's needs and related to its system of health care.The author's findings and recommendations are essential reading for everyone concerned with the health and development of emerging countries. Written in a clear, compelling style, the book is enhanced by illustrations by the young Thai artist, Praphan Srisouta.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPublic health administrationzDeveloping countries. 0aPublic healthzDeveloping countries. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061053608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174145640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501741456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501741456/original  a978-3-11-061053-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGB